 Current and former female agents spoke out to renounce depictions of CIA women on TV shows and in movies .
The women say they are nothing like the honey-pots on these shows who use their sexuality to ensnare terrorists and booze .
Retired CIA officer Sandra Grimes , 69 , who helped expose her colleague Aldrich Ames as a Russian double agent , says she sees nothing of herself in the characters of State of Affairs and Homeland .